which the Engli&s;h had projected in America. The King
of Sardinia &s;agaciou&s;ly kept aloof, re&s;olving, in imitation
of his predece&s;&s;ors, to maintain his power on a re&s;pectable
footing, and be ready to &s;ei&s;e all opportunities to extend
